# Account Context for review-transactions

Read this at the start of every run to correctly classify investment account activity.
Copy this file to account-context.md and fill in your own account details.

## Account structure

| Monarch account name | Type | Notes |
|---------------------|------|-------|
| `CHECKING (...1234)` | Checking | Primary spending account |
| `SAVINGS (...5678)` | Savings | Emergency fund |
| `401(K) PLAN (...0000)` | 401k | Employer plan |
| `ROTH IRA (...0000)` | Roth IRA | Individual retirement account |
| `Health Savings Account (...0000)` | HSA | Payroll contributions |

## Contribution / rollover chains

Document any recurring multi-step flows here so the skill understands the full
picture — e.g. mega backdoor Roth, 401k match, HSA employer contributions.

## Recurring transaction notes

Add any notes about specific merchants, account-specific rules, or categorization
context that helps the skill make better suggestions.
